# ppp — Personal and Pastoral Planning

## Stack
- SvelteKit (TypeScript)
- Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Edge Functions)
- Tailwind + shadcn-svelte
- Vercel (deployment)
- pdf-lib (Edge Functions for PDF generation)
- Resend (email)

## Naming Conventions
- Svelte components: PascalCase
- Routes: kebab-case
- Supabase tables: snake_case
- TypeScript types: PascalCase

## Architecture Defaults
- RLS enabled on all tables — fail closed
- Soft delete via deleted_at TIMESTAMPTZ on every table
- Audit log trigger on every table (trigger-driven, never app-layer writes)
- Svelte stores for state management

## Route Structure
- /dashboard
- /invoicing
- /invoicing/invoices
- /invoicing/invoices/[id]
- /library
- /library/add
- /library/books/[id]
- /projects
- /settings
- /settings/library
- /settings/invoicing
- /settings/audit-log
- /settings/profile

## Supabase Patterns
- Always filter WHERE deleted_at IS NULL unless explicitly querying deleted records
- Never write directly to audit_log from app layer
- Use Supabase Edge Functions for PDF generation and email — never from client
- Auth: email/password only (no magic link)
- Two users: owner (full access) + viewer (library write, calendar read, no invoicing/projects)

## Code Style
- No default exports except in +page.svelte and +layout.svelte (SvelteKit convention)
- Keep components small — extract when a component exceeds ~150 lines
- No inline styles — Tailwind classes only
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any`

## RLS & Security
- RLS enabled on every table — no exceptions
- Never expose service role key on the client — Edge Functions only
- All queries scoped to auth.uid() — never query across users
- viewer role checked via user_permissions table — owner bypasses entirely
- No direct table access from client for invoicing tables — owner only

## Data Integrity
- Every table gets deleted_at, created_at, updated_at, created_by unless documented exception
- Documented exceptions: audit_log, module_registry, bible_books, categories (static/system tables)
- soft delete only — no hard deletes from app layer
- revertible flag set at trigger level — never set from app layer